# Resolution 2007-12-29.jdd.1: Madwifi as an associated project

This resolution was adopted by the Board of Directors of SPI at their
meeting of [January 16, 2008](/meetings/minutes/2008/2008-01-16/).

This resolution is superseded by [2018-07-09.mm.1](../../2018/2018-07-09.mm.1).

### Whereas

1. Madwifi is a substantial and significant Free Software project.

2. The Madwifi developers would like SPI's support and assistance, including
taking donations.

### The SPI board resolves that

1. Madwifi is formally invited to become an SPI Associated Project, according
to the SPI Framework for Associated Projects.

2. Currently, Michael Renzmann (mrenzmann@madwifi.org) is recognised by SPI as
the current authoritative decision maker for Madwifi.

3. This invitation will lapse, if not accepted, 60 days after it is approved
by the SPI Board.

